akley-yukon-vet-advises-avc-students-177180/ |accessdate=6 March 2020 |work=www.theguardian.pe.ca |publisher=[[The Guardian (Charlottetown)|The Guardian]] |date=14 Jan 2018 |archiveurl=https://archive.is/wip/3AUl8 |archivedate=6 March 2020 |language=en}}</ref> and [[Haines, Alaska]]. Dr. Oakley  attended the [[Atlantic Veterinary College]] in [[Prince Edward Island]], [[Canada]]<ref name=\"RBlur01\">{{cite web |last1=Dehnart |first1=Andy |title=Dr. Oakley, Yukon Vet and her daughters on how they help animals while filming a reality show |url=https://www.realityblurred.com/realitytv/2018/10/dr-oakley-yukon-vet-dr-michelle-oakley-sierra-maya-interview/ |publisher=reality blurred |accessdate=6 March 2020 |archiveurl=https://archive.is/wip/oCnQJ |archivedate=6 March 2020 |date=5 October 2018}}</ref> and interned at the [[Calgary Zoo]].<ref name=\"TStar01\">{{cite news |last1=Brioux |first1=Bill |title=Yukon vet Dr. Michelle Oakley on the best part of working with wild animals |url=https://www.thestar.com/entertainment/television/2018/10/05/yukon-vet-dr-michelle-oakley-on-the-best-part-of-working-with-wild-animals.html |accessdate=6 March 2020 |agency=The Canadian Press |publisher=Toronto Star |date=5 October 2018 |archiveurl=https://archive.is/wip/rrDOs |archivedate=6 March 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{imdb title|tt3593456}}\n\n[[Category:National Geographic Channel original programming]]\n[[Category:Nature educational television series]]\n[[Category:2014 American television series debuts]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n\n\n{{Yukon-stub}}\n{{Canada-tv-prog-stub}}\n{{US-nonfiction-tv-prog-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox television\n| italic_title         = \n| show_name            = Dr. Oakley, Yukon Vet\n| image                = \n| image_upright        = \n| image_size           = \n| image_alt            = \n| caption              = \n| show_name_2          = \n| native_name          = <!-